summary: This is a travel authorization email from the DOJ's E2 travel system approving a trip for an investigator to travel to Los Angeles from December 15-18, 2019, for the purpose of conducting a witness interview related to the Epstein investigation.

events.title: Witness Interview Travel Authorization
events.description: Travel authorization was approved for a DOJ investigator to travel to Los Angeles, CA, for the purpose of conducting a witness interview related to the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID 11164814) was approved on April 16, 2020, for a trip related to the Epstein investigation.
The purpose of the trip was a witness interview, coded as 'R20NYS13444 - Epstein Investigation - Witness interview'.
The authorized travel was to Los Angeles, CA, from December 15 to December 18, 2019.
The document originates from the DOJ's internal E2 travel system, indicating official government investigative activity.
The email shows the investigation was active and involved witness interviews as of late 2019, after Epstein's death in August 2019.
